"null"
Manual Prepared Routes List Route List

Harry Lee, Thu 21/Jul/2011

Automatically generated control tables (partial information) are compared to the manually generated control tables, based on 5SetData for Westrol 4. Overlap analysis is based on overlap distance calculated according to the deceleration rate a, and the the route speed limit v.

Suppose the train is running at a speed of v, when a signal is spad-ed (signal passed at danger), and suppose the the train controller starts to stop the train immediately when the train spads. Suppose the deceleration rate applied is -a, then it takes the train t seconds to stop, where v, a, and t are related with the following equation:

v = a * t

within this time period, the distance travelled by the train is

s = a * t^2 / 2

eliminating the time t by combining the above two equations, we have

s = v^2/(2 * a)

This is the minimum overlap distance for the train. The deceleration can be set using the "Preferences" menu and then the "set decel..." menu ite. In this report, the deceleration rate a is set to be 1.1 m/s^2.

Under this condition, among the 992 routes, there are 396 routes which have overlap conditions. The overlap results were obtained by looking at the tracks in the succeeding routes. All the points that lay within the overlap distance are listed.

The program generated control tables contain such field as "points lock to normal", "points lock to reverse", which should be the same as "points normal" and "points reverse" in the manual control table. There are other fields, such as "points bring to normal", "points bring to reverse". These field contains extra information of points that should be bring to preferred position, such that the route is more safer.

Points to be locked in the overlaps are not included in the "point lock to normal" and "points lock to reverse", but are included in each overlap routes. We still have the problem for determining the correct overlap length for each route.
